Create the .sh file. Save it and name it according to your command. Say svc.sh

Change its mode. 
Give it execute permission. (chmod +x svc.sh)
Run it. (sh svc.sh)

Text file gets created.

Copy the .sh file to /usr/bin. (sudo cp svc.sh /usr/bin)

Command svc gets created. 
Now you can use it from any directory.

